From: claude[bot] <noreply@anthropic.com>
Subject: [PATCH] Methodology improvements for 2026-05-14 (workflow fixes)

The auto-improve workflow's GitHub App token does not carry `workflows`
permission, so it cannot push edits under .github/workflows/. Apply this
patch manually with `git apply improve-2026-05-14-workflow-fixes.patch`
from the repo root, then commit and push as the human owner.

This is the third consecutive iteration of the same fix
(see improve/2026-05-12, improve/2026-05-13). The single most valuable
follow-up is granting the daily-improve App `workflows: write` so it
self-applies. Context for what this fixes: see IMPROVEMENTS.md.

Verification done from inside the runner today (2026-05-14):
- 21 RSS feed URLs in the patch all return HTTP 200 with valid feed bodies.
- 10 Bluesky author handles in the patch all return HTTP 200.
- The legacy URLs being removed all confirmed broken:
    * ai.meta.com/blog/rss/                  HTTP 404
    * googleaiblog.blogspot.com/atom.xml     200 but frozen <updated>=2025-10-07
    * blog.research.google/atom.xml          200 but frozen <updated>=2025-10-07
    * openrss.org/www.anthropic.com/news     200 but content-type=text/html
    * public.api.bsky.app .../searchPosts    HTTP 403

Correction vs yesterday's improve/2026-05-13 patch: yesterday swapped the
broken googleaiblog.blogspot.com URL for blog.research.google/atom.xml,
which is *also* frozen. This patch uses research.google/blog/rss/ instead
(verified live, latest item dated within current week).

